@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<div class="container py-5">
    <div class="auth-card mx-auto shadow-lg" style="max-width: 900px; padding: 4rem;">
        <div class="text-center mb-5">
            <h1 class="fw-black text-dark" style="letter-spacing: -2px; font-size: 3rem;">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
            <p class="text-muted fw-bold">Effective Date: May 5, 2026</p>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-content fw-bold text-muted" style="line-height: 1.8;">
            <section class="mb-5">
                <h4 class="text-dark fw-black text-uppercase small mb-3" style="letter-spacing: 1px;">1. Overview</h4>
                <p>
                    Welcome to <strong>NipponQuest</strong>. We are committed to protecting your personal data and your privacy.
                    This policy outlines how we handle your information as you progress through our gamified Japanese language platform.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-5">
                <h4 class="text-dark fw-black text-uppercase small mb-3" style="letter-spacing: 1px;">2. Information Collection</h4>
                <p>To provide a personalized experience and maintain the integrity of our Player Economy, we collect the following:</p>
                <ul class="list-unstyled ps-3 border-start border-primary border-3">
                    <li class="mb-2"><strong>Identity Data:</strong> Your email address and chosen GamerTag.</li>
                    <li class="mb-2"><strong>Authentication Data:</strong> Profile information provided via Google third-party authentication.</li>
                    <li class="mb-2"><strong>Gamification Metrics:</strong> Records of your Level, XP, Gold, and League placement.</li>
                    <li class="mb-2"><strong>User-Generated Content:</strong> Flashcard decks, Anki import files (.apkg), and associated text/media you upload to the Discover Hub.</li>
                    <li class="mb-2"><strong>Economy Data:</strong> Transaction history for Gold exchanges, deck downloads, and marketplace interactions.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-5">
                <h4 class="text-dark fw-black text-uppercase small mb-3" style="letter-spacing: 1px;">3. Data Usage</h4>
                <p>Your information is used strictly to facilitate the competitive and educational features of the platform, including:</p>
                <ul class="list-unstyled">
                    <li class="mb-1"><i class="bi bi-check2-circle text-primary me-2"></i> Managing your character progression and Login Streaks.</li>
                    <li class="mb-1"><i class="bi bi-check2-circle text-primary me-2"></i> Generating global and local Arena Leaderboards.</li>
                    <li class="mb-1"><i class="bi bi-check2-circle text-primary me-2"></i> Hosting and distributing your published decks on the Discover Hub.</li>
                    <li class="mb-1"><i class="bi bi-check2-circle text-primary me-2"></i> Processing Player Economy transactions and Gold rewards securely.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-5">
                <h4 class="text-dark fw-black text-uppercase small mb-3" style="letter-spacing: 1px;">4. Security & Storage</h4>
                <p>
                    We utilize <strong>ASP.NET Core Identity</strong> and industry-standard encryption to protect your data.
                    Your authentication secrets are managed via secure environments to ensure zero exposure. Temporary files required for processing user uploads (such as Anki deck extractions) are routinely and securely deleted from our servers once processed.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-5">
                <h4 class="text-dark fw-black text-uppercase small mb-3" style="letter-spacing: 1px;">5. Your Rights</h4>
                <p>
                    As a user of NipponQuest, you maintain the right to access your data, update your GamerTag, remove your published decks from the Discover Hub, or request full account deletion.
                    Contact us directly for any data-related inquiries.
                </p>
            </section>

            <div class="mt-5 pt-4 border-top text-center">
                <p class="small opacity-75">
                    For legal or technical inquiries: <br />
                    <span class="text-dark fw-black">YugenLabs</span><br />
                    <span class="text-muted">Lead Developer: Joshua Marc Lourens</span><br />
                    Westville, South Africa
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>